# CLIENT_DOMAINS Environment Configuration Example
# This file demonstrates how to configure client domains via environment variables
# instead of hardcoding them in settings.py

# Method 1: Bulk configuration using JSON (recommended for multiple overrides)
# Set all custom domains at once using JSON format
# CLIENT_DOMAINS_JSON='{"R_REDMINE": "custom-redmine.yourdomain.com", "WTC": "intelliwiz.yourdomain.com", "SUKHI": "singapore.yourdomain.com"}'

# Method 2: Individual domain overrides (recommended for single client changes)
# Override specific client domains individually
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_R_REDMINE=custom-redmine.yourdomain.com
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_WTC=intelliwiz.yourdomain.com
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_SUKHI=singapore.yourdomain.com
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_D_SUKHI=demo.yourdomain.com

# Available client keys for individual overrides:
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_R_REDMINE      - Redmine production
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_R_TOURTRAX     - TourTrax production
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_R_SUKHI        - Sukhi production
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_R_CAPGEMINI    - Capgemini production
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_D_SUKHI        - Sukhi demo
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_D_CAPGEMINI    - Capgemini demo
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_SUKHI          - Sukhi Singapore
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_D_TOURTRAX     - TourTrax demo
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_WTC            - WTC production
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_R_YTPLD        - YTPLD production

# Example production environment:
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_WTC=prod.intelliwiz.com
# CLIENT_DOMAIN_SUKHI=sg.intelliwiz.com

# Example staging environment:
# CLIENT_DOMAINS_JSON='{"R_REDMINE": "staging-redmine.yourdomain.com", "WTC": "staging.yourdomain.com"}'

# Security Notes:
# - Domain names are validated for proper format
# - Maximum domain length is 255 characters
# - Only alphanumeric characters, hyphens, and dots are allowed
# - Invalid domains will be logged and excluded

# Deployment Notes:
# 1. Add these environment variables to your deployment configuration
# 2. For Docker: Add to docker-compose.yml environment section
# 3. For Kubernetes: Add to ConfigMap or Secret
# 4. For traditional deployments: Add to system environment or .env files
# 5. For cloud platforms: Add to environment configuration (AWS ECS/Lambda, GCP Cloud Run, etc.)